{
  "texts": [
    "However, since the similarity score of their connection is stronger with From 1's input field, we only keep those edges.As for text-to-text edges, we apply a statistical method for their retention.",
    "We compile the scores of all such edges and filter out those less than the threshold of 𝜇 + 𝜆.𝜎, where 𝜇 represents the mean score, 𝜎 the standard deviation, and 𝜆 is a predetermined factor set at 1 2.",
    "Again, in Figure 3, the feedback is connected to both From and To labels, although the connection to label To is not statistically significant for us to keep in the graph.",
    "After applying the filtering process, edges removed from the graph are indicated in red in Figure 3, while the remaining edges are shown in green.",
    "Relevant Input Context.Having established the textual context for each input field, the subsequent phase of our method identifies relevant inputs that are interrelated."
  ]
